# StandardRB Code Formatting

Always run `bin/standardrb --fix` before committing code changes to ensure consistent code formatting and style compliance.

## When to run StandardRB
- Before every commit that includes Ruby files (`.rb`)
- After making changes to Ruby code
- When working with Ruby files in any capacity

## How to apply formatting
```bash
bin/standardrb --fix
```

## What StandardRB does
- Enforces consistent Ruby style guidelines
- Converts double quotes to single quotes where appropriate
- Ensures proper indentation and spacing
- Applies consistent formatting across the codebase
- Helps maintain code quality and readability

## Integration with commit process
StandardRB formatting should be applied as part of the pre-commit workflow, ensuring all Ruby code meets the project's style standards before being committed.
